As the commander of Rhodes Island, you must direct your Operators in a battle against Faust, one of the leaders of Reunion. Be careful.  
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical Damage to our units.

main_06-07.name: It Fell From the Sky!
main_06-07.description: The legendary Yeti Squadron, an elite anti-Ursus squad of Infected, has appeared in a Chernobog sub-city. Their fighting style is unlike any Reunion forces we've encountered before, so make sure not to underestimate them.

main_06-07#f#.name: It Fell From the Sky!
main_06-07#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The Speed of enemy units is increased significantly

tr_16.name: Harsh Environment
tr_16.description: Learn about the "Cold" and "Frozen" status effects.

main_06-08.name: Different Perspective
main_06-08.description: The Yeti Squadron, in addition to fielding casters that specialize in ice-based Arts, has also released Originium Slugs that explode in a shower of rime upon death. Please exercise caution.

main_06-08#f#.name: Different Perspective
main_06-08#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Yeti Squadron units and Frostfangs deal even more damage against Frozen units.

main_06-09.name: Bells of Liberation
main_06-09.description: The icecleavers, a special group of combatants of the Yeti Squad, deal massive damage to frozen Operators. Stay calm when fighting them.

main_06-09#f#.name: Bells of Liberation
main_06-09#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Enemy Yeti Icecleavers have greatly increased HP and ASPD.

main_06-10.name: "Times Like These"
main_06-10.description: A large number of Yeti Squadron troops have launched an offensive against us, and an arduous battle looms ahead. Make good use of our Operators' various strengths and aim to defeat the enemy.

main_06-10#f#.name: "Times Like These"
main_06-10#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
7 tiles on the map will no longer allow units to be deployed upon them.

main_06-11.name: Snow Upon the Tundra
main_06-11.description:
The Yeti Squadron has placed special Originium facilities around the battlefield. Please be prepared to respond accordingly. 
<@lv.item><Originium Ice Crystal></> Periodically releases a frigid wave that will inflict Cold to affected allied units.

main_06-11#f#.name: Snow Upon the Tundra
main_06-11#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Originium Ice Crystals release frigid waves more frequently.

st_06-02.name: No Light Without Fire
st_06-02.description: She has never forgotten about that certain place…

main_06-12.name: Frost Upon the Tundra
main_06-12.description:
The "Oneiros" drones controlled by the Yeti Squad are capable of inflicting Arts damage in an area upon our Operators, as well as inflicting the Cold status. Please prioritize taking them down.
<@lv.item><Originium Ice Crystal></> Periodically releases a frigid wave that will inflict Cold to affected allied units.

main_06-12#f#.name: Frost Upon the Tundra
main_06-12#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Enemy Oneiros drones have greatly increased movement speed.

main_06-13.name: Nostalgia
main_06-13.description: Enemy icecleavers have been spotted in conjunction with Oneiros drones. As this will surely be a very difficult battle, please plan carefully to deal with various status abnormalities and enemy attacks.

main_06-13#f#.name: Nostalgia
main_06-13#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Enemy Oneiros drones have reduced range, but greatly increased HP and DEF.

main_06-14.name: Black Rabbit, White Rabbit
main_06-14.description: Before us stands the commander of the Yeti Squadron, FrostNova, enhanced with a terrifying power we've never seen before. As she is one of the strongest warriors in Reunion, we must utilize every bit of our strength to overcome her.

main_06-15.name: Winter's End
main_06-15.description: We chose to fight to the bitter end. She did as well.

st_06-03.name: Only You Know
st_06-03.description: She has never forgotten about that night…

st_07-01.description: A person walks into the sunset, alone.

main_07-01.name: Night of Farewells
main_07-01.description: Remnants of Reunion’s forces remain entrenched in the streets of Lungmen, desperately resisting to the bitter end. Prepare for combat.

main_07-01#f#.name: Night of Farewells
main_07-01#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Possessed Veteran Junkmen and Possessed Soldier Leaders have greatly increased HP.

main_07-02.name: Renegade Blade
main_07-02.description: Mephisto’s Herd is no longer under the control of its leader, but their bottomless aggression has prompted them to attack Rhodes Island’s ship. Put them out of their misery.

main_07-02#f#.name: Renegade Blade
main_07-02#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The DEF of allied units is halved.

main_07-03.name: Side by Side-1
main_07-03.description: The spearhead of Reunion’s reconnaissance force has appeared at the location where we established a concealed facility. Be careful, these are no ordinary Reunion grunts that we’re dealing with.

main_07-03#f#.name: Side by Side-1
main_07-03#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
All enemies have increased Movement Speed.

main_07-04.name: Side by Side-2
main_07-04.description: Various Reunion members patrol the passages of the hub layer in the heart of Chernobog. Don’t take them lightly; their uniforms... are the same as the Infected guerillas that once fought int he northern plains of Ursus.

main_07-04#f#.name: Side by Side-2
main_07-04#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The DP Cost of Ranged units is doubled.

tr_17.name: Focused Strike
tr_17.description: Learn how to counter the commanding tactics of Reunion’s guerrilla forces.

main_07-05.name: Forgotten Lands
main_07-05.description: We’ve encountered guerilla messengers on our way to the central area of the core city. They employ a unique method of communication and commanding, and we may perhaps be able to draw some inspiration from fighting against them...

st_07-02.description: A knot that, to this day, has still not been untied.

main_07-06.name: Fury of the Silent-1
main_07-06.description:
We’ve found a strange Sarkaz Originium altar in the hub layer... The altar seems to have a strange effect upon the surrounding environment, but we can also leverage it to mount a defense against the enemy.
<@lv.item><Originium Altar></>Periodically emits Pulse Waves to the surrounding tiles, damaging both allied and enemy units.

main_07-07.name: Fury of the Silent-2
main_07-07.description:
Our enemies are no longer fighting in the characteristic style of scattered guerillas. Now is a head-on clash between tactics. Formulate your combat strategy appropriately, and deal a critical blow to the enemy.
<@lv.item><Originium Altar></>Periodically emits Pulse Waves to the surrounding tiles, damaging both allied and enemy units.

main_07-07#f#.name: Fury of the Silent-2
main_07-07#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Guerrilla Heralds have greatly increased HP.

main_07-08.name: Flames of the Faint
main_07-08.description:
Sarkaz warriors have entered the battlefield, but be wary - they don’t seem to be from the same faction as the guerillas. They even seem to draw inspiration from the Originium altars...?!
<@lv.item><Originium Altar></>Periodically emits Pulse Waves to the surrounding tiles, damaging both allied and enemy units.

main_07-08#f#.name: Flames of the Faint
main_07-08#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Mercenary Sarkaz Fighters have greatly increased ASPD.

main_07-09.name: Stained-1
main_07-09.description:
Sarkaz Casters have appeared on the battlefield, and it seems like the Originium Altars may be affecting their Arts. However, don’t panic - we have ways of dealing with them.
<@lv.item><Originium Altar></>Periodically emits Pulse Waves to the surrounding tiles, damaging both allied and enemy units.

main_07-09#f#.name: Stained-1
main_07-09#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Enemies have -60% Movement Speed, and greatly increased HP and ATK.

main_07-10.name: Stained-2
main_07-10.description:
As Reunion’s elite warriors, the Sarkaz Mercenaries have shown formidable strength. Only by defeating them can we continue forward.
<@lv.item><Originium Altar>Periodically emits Pulse Waves to the surrounding tiles, damaging both allied and enemy units.
<@lv.item><Roadblock></> Deploy to block the enemy's route

main_07-11.name: Aegis of the Infected-1
main_07-11.description: The horn has been sounded. Face the legendary guerillas of Ursus, and turn their own tactics against them! However, those heavily-armored guerilla warriors are indeed the most terrifying combatants of the Ursus army...

main_07-11#f#.name: Aegis of the Infected-1
main_07-11#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Sniper and Guard Operators cannot be deployed.

main_07-12.name: Guerilla-1
main_07-12.description: The mortars used by the guerillas pose a significant threat to us. These weapons taken from Ursus’s military arsenal are terrifying incarnations of the very essence of war.

main_07-12#f#.name: Guerilla-1
main_07-12#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
All enemies have significantly increased ATK.

main_07-13.name: Guerilla-2
main_07-13.description: The guerillas’ Vertical Strike Squad has withstood harsh trials and brutal wars. They’ve fought Ursus for more than a decade, and their will is nigh indomitable. We have but a single moment for a chance at victory.

main_07-13#f#.name: Guerilla-2
main_07-13#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Guerilla Shieldguards have 66% lower Max HP, but have 50% increased DEF and RES.

main_07-14.name: Unrivaled
main_07-14.description: Who has witnessed a battle like this before? Who can survive such a battlefield? Even a simple skirmish has struck fear into our hearts. We do not have the ability to defeat them. We must escape to where they cannot see us.

main_07-14#f#.name: Unrivaled
main_07-14#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Maximum squad size is reduced to 7 Operators.

main_07-15.name: Aegis of the Infected-2
main_07-15.description:
We cannot destroy them, so we will do our best not to be destroyed by them. We must achieve a tactical victory. We strive to paralyze their spinal cord and expose the giant’s head to us.
<@lv.item><Originium Altar></>Periodically emits Pulse Waves to the surrounding tiles, damaging both allied and enemy units.

main_07-15#f#.name: Aegis of the Infected-2
main_07-15#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Guard and Caster Operators cannot be deployed.

main_07-16.name: Death of a Patriot
main_07-16.description:
They are commanded by the “Aegis” of the Infected. The most ancient bloodline among the warriors of Sarkaz. Ursus’s indomitable incarnation of war. The backbone of the Reunion Movement. Yelena’s father.
<@lv.item><Originium Altar></>Periodically emits Pulse Waves to the surrounding tiles, damaging both allied and enemy units.
<@lv.item><Interference Mine></>Upon explosion, deals heavy damage to enemies in the surrounding tiles and amplifies the damage they take for 15 seconds.

main_07-16#f#.name: Death of a Patriot
main_07-16#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
6 tiles on the battlefield are no longer available for deployment.

st_07-03.description: It’s like a city driving towards finality.

st_07-04.description: Throw open the doors that lead to this world.

main_08-01.name: Yesterday, the Chaff Cracked
main_08-01.description:
In the remote tundra, patrol squads, dressed in black beetle-like uniforms, comb through remote villages to hunt down the Infected. 
<@lv.item><Static Roadblock></>Blocks the movement of Ursus Civilians and Talulah, the Fighter; Can be destroyed by your units.

main_08-01#f#.description:

3 tiles on the battlefield are no longer available for deployment.

st_08-01.name: Today, Sanguine Overlows
st_08-01.description: 10:32:09 The war continues, but the situation has changed.

tr_18.name: Civilian Evacuation
tr_18.description:
Learn how to evacuate civilians from conflict zones. 
<@lv.item><Static Roadblock></>Blocks the movement of Ursus Civilians and Talulah, the Fighter; Can be destroyed by your units. 
<@lv.item><Ursus Civilian></>Depletes an HP Seal when killed by an enemy.

main_08-02.name: Innocent Flesh and Blood
main_08-02.description:
In the tundras of Ursus, every living creature is under suspicion. They may be murderers, thugs, spies, or simply innocents. 
<@lv.item><Static Roadblock></>Blocks the movement of Ursus Civilians and Talulah, the Fighter; Can be destroyed by your units. 
<@lv.item><Ursus Civilian></>Depletes an HP Seal when killed by an enemy.

main_08-03.name: Oatstalk, Easily Alight
main_08-03.description:
Righteous anger from witnessing such brutality is justified. Ursus’s manglers are well-trained, and their fangs do not cease just because of their victims’ emotions. 
<@lv.item><Static Roadblock></>Blocks the movement of Ursus Civilians and Talulah, the Fighter; Can be destroyed by your units. 
<@lv.item><Talulah, the Fighter></>Depletes an HP Seal when killed by an enemy.

main_08-03#f#.name: Oatstalk, Easily Alight
main_08-03#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
The DP Cost of Ranged units is doubled.

st_08-02.name: Silence, Born of Excessive Speech
st_08-02.description: Kal’tsit has never demonstrated impatience when explaining a story to others. She is either very good at controlling herself, or she actually enjoys it.

main_08-04.name: Sparks, Extinguished in a Touch
main_08-04.description:
Sometimes, protecting others is not a goal, but a process. Also, Ursus’s crossbowmen also privately believe that killing others is not a goal, but a process. 
<@lv.item><Static Roadblock></>Blocks the movement of Ursus Civilians and Talulah, the Fighter; Can be destroyed by your units.
<@lv.item><Ursus Civilian></>Depletes an HP Seal when killed by an enemy.

st_08-03.name: Death, Comes When Beckoned
st_08-03.description: In reality, just witnessing an atrocity is enough to make one become a part of it.

main_08-05.name: Cold, Only Perceived
main_08-05.description:
The lowest recorded temperatures of the Northwestern Tundras are sometimes not as bone-chilling as the words of certain individuals. 
<@lv.item><Talulah, the Fighter></>Depletes an HP Seal when killed by an enemy.
<@lv.item><FrostNova’s Originium Ice Crystal></>Periodically releases a frigid wave that will inflict Cold on affected enemy units.

main_08-05#f#.name: Cold, Only Perceived
main_08-05#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Ursus Raiders have significantly increased ATK and DEF.

st_08-04.name: Will, Phantom Wisps
st_08-04.description: All ideals, once transmitted, will eventually be corrupted or altered. Only through practice can an ideal be proven, and as we know, once something happens, it cannot be undone.

main_08-06.name: War, Sprawling Without Cease
main_08-06.description:
The mightiest and meekest both share the same tenacity. 
<@lv.item><Talulah, the Fighter></>Depletes an HP Seal when killed by an enemy.
<@lv.item><Patriot’s Originium Altar></>Periodically releases gas in the surrounding 4 tiles, inflicting heavy damage to enemies.

main_08-06#f#.name: War, Sprawling Without Cease
main_08-06#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Ursus Armored Casters have significantly increased attack range.

st_08-05.name: Ruination, Long Awaited
st_08-05.description: With enough effort, drops of water can pierce through stone. Everything you’ve experienced will coalesce into the truth and spread across this land.

main_08-07.name: Baptism by Tractor Fire
main_08-07.description:
Within the Ursus Army, the history of the Artillery Corps is not particularly lengthy. They are more than happy to arm themselves with the newest technology, and have little concern to spare for who their enemies are. 
<@lv.item><Static Roadblock></>Blocks the movement of Ursus Civilians and Talulah, the Fighter; Can be destroyed by your units.
<@lv.item><Ursus Civilian></>Depletes an HP Seal when killed by an enemy.

main_08-07#f#.name: Baptism by Tractor Fire
main_08-07#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Imperial Artillery Targeteers have greatly increased HP.

main_08-08.name: The Heart, Fickle and Impermanent
main_08-08.description:
If you wish to prove yourself before a legend, you must first <@lv.sp>approach perfection</>. Only the commoners shall bleed. Only the noble shall face slander. 
<@lv.item><Static Roadblock></>Blocks the movement of Ursus Civilians and Talulah, the Fighter; Can be destroyed by your units.
<@lv.item><Talulah, the Fighter></>Depletes an HP Seal when killed by an enemy.

main_08-08#f#.name: The Heart, Fickle and Impermanent
main_08-08#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Your units have significantly decreased ATK.

main_08-09.name: Farewell, to Reunite Once More
main_08-09.description: 07:29:28 Though some friends may be willing to share your pain, you should perhaps <@lv.sp>reach out to them</>. And some may never have been your friends in the first place.

main_08-09#f#.name: Farewell, to Reunite Once More
main_08-09#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Enraged Possessed Soldiers, Enraged Possessed Leaders, and Enraged Possessed Bonethrowers have increased ASPD.

main_08-10.name: Reunited, Only to Separate
main_08-10.description:
To lose. 
<@lv.item><Static Roadblock></>Blocks the movement of Ursus Civilians and Talulah, the Fighter; Can be destroyed by your units.
<@lv.item><Ursus Civilian></>Depletes an HP Seal when killed by an enemy.

main_08-11.name: Silent Butcher
main_08-11.description:
The Empire of Ursus has lost many elites throughout its many wars, but is always able to cultivate more. Just as an empire should. 
<@lv.item><Roadblock> Deploy to block the enemy's route.
<@lv.item><Ursus Civilian></>Depletes an HP Seal when killed by an enemy.

main_08-12.name: Malediction, Bound for Retribution
main_08-12.description: She has not yet died, but she has already seen too much death.

main_08-12#f#.name: Malediction, Bound for Retribution
main_08-12#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Sarkaz Centurion Hosts have significantly increased lifesteal.

main_08-13.name: Snowfall, Blackening the Earth
main_08-13.description:
Yet, they do not regard anyone as an “enemy.” The dead and the incompetent have never been among their ranks. 
<@lv.item><Static Roadblock></>Blocks the movement of Ursus Civilians and Talulah, the Fighter; Can be destroyed by your units.
<@lv.item><Talulah, the Fighter></>Depletes an HP Seal when killed by an enemy.

main_08-13#f#.name: Snowfall, Blackening the Earth
main_08-13#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Imperial Strikers and Elite Imperial Strikers have increased ATK and HP.

main_08-14.name: Awakening, a Dream's End
main_08-14.description: An origin, a purpose, a fate, a demise. A tragedy that claims the Herd, all of them. Who can truly <@lv.sp>choose</> their own life?

main_08-14#f#.name: Awakening, a Dream's End
main_08-14#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Toxic dust from Mephisto, “The Singer,” deals significantly increased damage.

main_08-15.name: Ire, Flowing Wilderward
main_08-15.description: “So I wish to make a wager with you.”

main_08-16.name: Behold, the Twilight Comes
main_08-16.description:
Memory and reality have both been completely released, and she knows her time has come. 
(Part of this story cannot be skipped the first time you experience it.)
<@lv.item><Heat Pump Passage></>Periodically deals great damage to any units on it.

main_08-16#f#.name: Behold, the Twilight Comes
main_08-16#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Talulah begins in the Enraged state.

main_08-17.name: Arise, Treading Through Flames
main_08-17.description:
06:26:33 <@lv.sp>Split flame with sword</>, defeat the past with the present, and confront the chaotic with one’s self. Rage, and know no compromise. Rage, and keep no silence. 
<@lv.item><Energy Aggregate></>Releases fireballs in the four cardinal directions, dealing Arts damage and inflicting [Burning Breath] (Deals increasing True damage each second, but can be resisted)

main_08-17#f#.name: Arise, Treading Through Flames
main_08-17#f#.description:
<@lv.fs>Condition:</>
Summons:Energy Aggregates deal increased Arts damage.

descList.2: Every journey has a <@lv.sp>■</>, but this world knows no<@lv.sp>■</>.
descList.3: Every journey has a destination, but this world knows no end.

sub_03-1-1.name: Lurking-1
sub_03-1-1.description: Please pay attention to the joint attack of enemy's invisible units and Casters.

sub_03-1-2.name: Lurking-2
sub_03-1-2.description: Enemy only focuses their attack on one spot, but still it's recommended to deploy Operators in the rear.

sub_03-2-1.name: Recon-1
sub_03-2-1.description:
Making good use of the Bushes and the Detector is the key to victory.
<@lv.item><Bush></> Operators deployed on it will not be targeted by enemy's ranged attack
<@lv.item><Detector></> Once activated, it will disable the invisibility of nearby enemies for a certain period

sub_03-2-2.name: Recon-2
sub_03-2-2.description:
Enemies are attacking from different routes this time. Please make sure you have enough melee Operators to stop them.
<@lv.item><Bush></> Operators deployed on it will not be targeted by enemy's ranged attack

sub_03-2-3.name: Recon-3
sub_03-2-3.description: The route is simple this time. It will be a test for your Operators' strength.

sub_03-3-1.name: Ignition-1
sub_03-3-1.description: This battle requires us to concentrate our firepower upon swarms of enemies.

sub_03-3-2.name: Concealed-1
sub_03-3-2.description: A large number of invisible enemies have surrounded the battlefield. Prepare to face them with a solid frontline and far-sighted scouts.

sub_04-1-1.name: Cluster-1
sub_04-1-1.description:
Make good use of the Active Originium in the middle of the battlefield and things will be much easier.
<@lv.item><Active Originium></> Operators deployed on it and enemies who have passed it will take constant damage, but their ATK and Attack Speed will be increased significantly

sub_04-1-2.name: Cluster-2
sub_04-1-2.description:
Enemies are coming from more directions. Still it's recommended to build your defense around the Active Originium.
<@lv.item><Active Originium></> Operators deployed on it and enemies who have passed it will take constant damage, but their ATK and Attack Speed will be increased significantly

sub_04-1-3.name: Cluster-3
sub_04-1-3.description:
The alien force has split into two. It may be a good choice to consume their HP by the Active Originium.
<@lv.item><Active Originium></> Operators deployed on it and enemies who have passed it will take constant damage, but their ATK and Attack Speed will be increased significantly

sub_04-2-1.name: Myriapoda-1
sub_04-2-1.description: Please be careful of the Originium Slugs in the south and the north and don't let them go through our defense.

sub_04-2-2.name: Myriapoda-2
sub_04-2-2.description: The battlefield is narrow this time. Please think carefully about where to deploy Operators.

sub_04-2-3.name: Myriapoda-3
sub_04-2-3.description: The battlefield is even narrower. It's recommended to upgrade Operators to get through it.

sub_04-3-1.name: Rage-1
sub_04-3-1.description: Please pay attention to the joint attack of enemy's Originium Slugs and alien elite Casters.

sub_04-3-2.name: Rage-2
sub_04-3-2.description: Scatter the Operators and use ranged Operators to take out the Originium Slugs from afar.

sub_04-3-3.name: Rage-3
sub_04-3-3.description: There is not much space for melee Operators this time. Try using Specialist Operators to cope with the tough enemies on the left.

sub_04-4-1.name: Stand Firm-1
sub_04-4-1.description: A large number of elite enemies have appeared. Please be careful.

sub_05-1-1.name: Entrenched-1
sub_05-1-1.description: The enemies continue their massed assault. Beware of the Wraiths sneaking in from above.

sub_05-1-2.name: Entrenched-2
sub_05-1-2.description: The situation in the field is getting more complicated. Carefully deploy melee Operators to stop the swarm of enemy Breakers.

sub_05-2-1.name: Biting Cold-1
sub_05-2-1.description: Well armored Frost Drones are causing havoc with our forces. Counter them with Caster Operators.

sub_05-2-2.name: Biting Cold-2
sub_05-2-2.description:
The enemy force is a mix of Arts Masters and Frost Drones making it increasingly difficult to handle. Make use of Sniper and Caster Operators and don't forget our Jammers! 
<@lv.item><Jammer></> can stop nearby enemy drones from firing, greatly reduce their speed, and prevent them from activating special abilities after being deployed.

sub_05-3-1.name: Panic-1
sub_05-3-1.description:
Possessed Soldier Leaders can regenerate faster and pose a serious threat. Take them out first. 
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical Damage to our units.

sub_05-3-2.name: Panic-2
sub_05-3-2.description:
Defense Crushers are enemy elite units specialized in defense. Their attacks can also stun our melee units. Take advantage of their slow moving speed to counter them. 
<@lv.item><Turrets></> periodically fire bolts, dealing Physical Damage to our units.

sub_05-4-1.name: Hover-1
sub_05-4-1.description:
A large number of unmanned enemy drones have appeared on this operation. Please take charge of the anti-air defense.
<@lv.item><Jammer></> Stops nearby enemy drones from firing, greatly reduces their speed, and prevents them from activating special abilities.

sub_05-4-2.name: Hover-2
sub_05-4-2.description: Enemies attack from different directions in this battle. Be careful of the large number of Casters that are approaching.

sub_05-4-3.name: Abnormality-1
sub_05-4-3.description: A number of possessed enemies have appeared during this battle. Please make sure to fortify your defenses.

sub_06-1-1.name: Condensation-1
sub_06-1-1.description: The Yeti Squadron is utilizing Infused Glacial Originium Slugs in their assault upon us. Please be careful of these aberrant creatures.

sub_06-1-2.name: Condensation-2
sub_06-1-2.description: A failure to handle the synergy between Infused Glacial Originium Slugs and Icecleavers will result in massive losses.

sub_06-2-1.name: Hoarfrost-1
sub_06-2-1.description: An attack from a large number of Infused Glacial Originium Slugs, followed by a wave of Icecleavers, will inflict catastrophic damage to insufficiently prepared squads.

sub_06-2-2.name: Hoarfrost-2
sub_06-2-2.description:
